This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with meta-reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel meta-learning algorithm that improves upon existing methods, which is a common theme in machine learning research. 

The paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as meta-learning is a technique used in AI to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of learning algorithms. 

Furthermore, the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics) as reinforcement learning is commonly used in robotics to train agents to perform tasks. 

The sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) may also be relevant as the paper deals with controlling the statistical distance of policies during meta-policy search. 

Finally, the paper may be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as reinforcement learning is also used in computer vision tasks such as object detection and image segmentation.
